item.title: HELP! im making a server but it wont go online!
item.dc:creator: @chassy13 Chassy13
item.description:
@chassy13 wrote:

[quote=“jc22493, post:11, topic:258805”][quote author=jc22493 link=topic=341750.msg2643773#msg2643773 date=1233086637]

Hello i am making a server (moparscape) but nobody can get on.ive portforwarded it has a no-ip it is called (templeofdeath.no-ip.info) ive tryed putting it on server statuses like codefasga but it says __Please correct these errors:
The server could not be contacted
what do i do now?

You probably leeched a source…so don’t say that you are “making” a server.
[/quote]Well duh you’ve leeched heaps.[/quote]
Everyone has leeched, but it depends on how much you leech. All these sources are technically leeched from RuneScape…
[/quote]

Who truly gives a shit? 99% of us leeched some source and edited to our liking. Don’t call other people a leecher when you probably did the same thing.

As for [quote=“dsv.13, post:8, topic:258805”]look in your firewall and let port 43594 trhough[/quote]

That actually does make a difference Digital Hotdogs. If port 43594 is not open, the firewall will block connections attempting to connect to it.

Turn your firewall off and review what you added. You most likely made a typo or missed a step. (If you don’t feel safe turning your firewall off, just add an exception)
